Class Tensor

java.lang.Object
com.flag4j.core.TensorBase<T,​T,​W,​W,​Y,​D,​X>
com.flag4j.core.dense.DenseTensorBase<T,​W,​T,​double[],​Double>
com.flag4j.core.dense.RealDenseTensorBase<Tensor,​CTensor>
com.flag4j.Tensor
All Implemented Interfaces:
DenseMixin<Double>, RealTensorMixin<Tensor,​CTensor>, TensorComparisonsMixin, TensorExclusiveMixin<Tensor,​Tensor,​SparseTensor,​CTensor>, TensorManipulationsMixin<Tensor>, TensorOperationsMixin<Tensor,​Tensor,​CTensor,​CTensor,​Tensor,​Double>, TensorPropertiesMixin, Serializable
public class Tensor extends RealDenseTensorBase<Tensor,​CTensor> implements TensorExclusiveMixin<Tensor,​Tensor,​SparseTensor,​CTensor>
Real Dense Tensor. May have any rank (that is, may have any number of unique axes/dimensions).

    • equals

      public boolean equals​(Object object)
      Checks if an object is equal to this tensor object. Valid object types are: Tensor, CTensor, SparseTensor, and SparseCTensor. These tensors are equal to this tensor if all entries are numerically equal to the corresponding element of this tensor. If the tensor is complex, then the imaginary component must be zero to be equal.
      Specified by:
      equals in interface TensorComparisonsMixin
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      object - Object to check equality with this tensor.
      Returns:
      True if the two tensors are numerically equivalent and false otherwise.

      public Tensor dot​(Tensor src2)

      public Tensor transpose​(int... axes)
      Computes the transpose of this tensor. That is, interchanges the axes of this tensor so that it matches the specified axes permutation. Same as T(int[]).
      Specified by:
      transpose in interface TensorExclusiveMixin<Tensor,​Tensor,​SparseTensor,​CTensor>

      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If axes is not a permutation of {1, 2, 3, ... N-1}.
